params.newKernel_: Address of the new kernel contract.

returns.dependencies: Array of keycodes which represent modules that                      this policy depends on.

params.safe: Safe which the message is targeted for.

params.signature: Signature byte array associated with the data.

params.dataHash: Hash of the data to be signed.
params.signature: Signature byte array associated with the data hash.

params.requests: Keycode <> function selector pairs which define the module access                 requested by a policy.

params.activate_: Whether to activate or deactivate the policy.

params.interfaceId: The interface identifier, as specified in ERC-165.

changeKernel(address).notice: Points the adapter to reference a new kernel address. This function can         only be called by the active kernel, and is used to perform migrations by         telling all policies and modules where the new kernel is located before         actually performing the migration.

configureDependencies().notice: Upon policy activation, configures the modules that the policy depends on.         If a module is ever upgraded that this policy depends on, the kernel will         call this function again to ensure this policy has the current address         of the module.

getMessageHashForSafe(address,bytes).notice: Returns the hash of a message that can be signed by safe owners.

isValidSignature(bytes,bytes).notice: Legacy implementation of `isValidSignature` to be compatible with gnosis         safe. Determines whether the signature provided is valid for the data hash.

isValidSignature(bytes32,bytes).notice: Standard EIP-1271 implementation that determines whether the signature         provided is valid for the data hash. Used as a wrapper around the         legacy gnosis safe implementation.

onERC1155BatchReceived(address,address,u.notice: Handles the callback when receiving multiple ERC1155 tokens.

onERC1155Received(address,address,uint25.notice: Handles the callback when receiving ERC1155 tokens.

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.notice: Handles the callback when receiving ERC721 tokens.

requestPermissions().notice: When a policy is activated, it must respond with a series of         keycode <> function selector pairs which represent a request for the         policy to call a specific function selector at a specific module.         These requests are stored as a mapping in the kernel while the policy         is active, and the kernel will reject any call from a policy to a module         which has not first requested permission.

setActiveStatus(bool).notice: Allows the kernel to grant or revoke the active status of the policy.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Implements support for IERC165, IERC721TokenReceiver, and IERC1155TokenReceiver.

tokensReceived(address,address,address,u.notice: Handles the callback when receiving ERC777 tokens.
